	<text>
		<body>
			<pb n="1"/>
				<p rend="align(right)"><placeName>New Albany Ind.</placeName> <date>August 21&#44; 54</date>&#39;</p>
				<p><addressee>Mr. Leeser</addressee></p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">I desire you again to change the address<lb/> of the Occident to me.  Instead of sending<lb/> it to this place&#44; send it to me in <placeName>Louisville<lb/> Ky.</placeName></p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">As you may still feel some interest in the fate<lb/> of your old correspondent and &#8220;Talmid&#44;&#8221; I will<lb/> inform you that I expect in a few days to pass<lb/> over to <placeName>Louisville</placeName> and take charge of the <placeName>Walnut<lb/> Street</placeName> Presbyterian Church.  I wish still to be a<lb/> reader of the Occident&#44; and I hold myself ready while<lb/> I remain in <placeName>Louisville</placeName> to do you any favor which<lb/> may be in my power.  I would be happy to receive<lb/> any communication from you.</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">If you see <persName>Mr. Henry Goldsmith</persName> I wish you<lb/> would remember to tell him that I am sorry that he<lb/> never thought it worth the trouble to answer my<lb/> letter to him written long ago.</p>
			<p rend="indent(9)">Yours most respectfully</p>
			<p rend="indent(11)"><persName role="author">M. R. Miller</persName>.</p>
				<p><addressee>Rev Isaac Leeser</addressee></p>
